#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga"
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21. Paṭhamakoṭigāmasutta → vijjā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Paṭhamakoṭigāmasutta"
msgstr "21. At the Village of Koṭi (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.21:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati koṭigāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis at the village "
"of Koṭi."

msgctxt "sn56.21:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn56.21:1.3"
msgid ""
"“catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasaccānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, not understanding and not comprehending four noble truths, both "
"you and I have wandered and transmigrated for such a very long time."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.432"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.21:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.2"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering,"

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.3"
msgid "Dukkhasamudayassa ariyasaccassa … pe …"
msgstr "the origin of suffering,"

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.4"
msgid "dukkhanirodhassa ariyasaccassa … pe …"
msgstr "the cessation of suffering,"

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.5"
msgid ""
"dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā "
"evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "sn56.21:2.6"
msgid ""
"Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, "
"dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ "
"ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ "
"anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ; ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti; natthi dāni "
"punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr ""
"These noble truths of suffering, origin, cessation, and the path have been "
"understood and comprehended. Craving for continued existence has been cut "
"off; the attachment to continued existence is ended; now there are no more "
"future lives.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.21:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn56.21:3.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.1"
msgid "“Catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Because of not truly seeing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.2"
msgid "Yathābhūtaṃ adassanā;"
msgstr "the four noble truths,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Saṃsitaṃ → saṃsaraṃ (bj) | saṃsaritaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.3"
msgid "Saṃsitaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ,"
msgstr "we have transmigrated for a long time"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:4.4"
msgid "Tāsu tāsveva jātisu."
msgstr "from one rebirth to the next."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: Tāni → yāni (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.1"
msgid "Tāni etāni diṭṭhāni,"
msgstr "But now that these truths have been seen,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.2"
msgid "bhavanetti samūhatā;"
msgstr "the attachment to rebirth is eradicated."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.3"
msgid "Ucchinnaṃ mūlaṃ dukkhassa,"
msgstr "The root of suffering is cut off,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.4"
msgid "natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr "now there are no more future lives.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.21:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
